arguments.name: Dark Mode Implementation
arguments.problem_statement: Users experience eye strain in low-light environments, leading to reduced app engagement and satisfaction. Implementing a dark mode feature will address this by providing a visually comfortable interface.
arguments.success_criteria: Dark mode is enabled by 80% of users within 2 weeks of launch, with a 15% increase in session duration during evening hours.

arguments.title: Switched from polling to WebSockets for real-time notifications
arguments.content: We decided to use WebSockets instead of polling for real-time notifications. This provides lower latency and better scalability compared to polling, which can lead to excessive server load and unnecessary network traffic. Tradeoffs considered included increased complexity in the client-side implementation and potential challenges with maintaining WebSocket connections in mobile environments. However, the benefits in real-time communication outweigh these concerns.
